System state changed.script:
{Log("EVENT: System state changed")}

{_ Context }
{SetState('eddi_context_last_subject', 'system')}
{SetState('eddi_context_last_action', 'change_state')}
{SetState('eddi_context_system', event.system)}
{SetState('eddi_context_system_system', event.system)}

{_ if homesystem.name = "Shinrarta Dezhra": {set homesystem to SystemDetails("Schin-rahta") - noch einzutragen _}

{_ Set up our system name}
{  if event.system = homesystem.name: {set system to OneOf('{(event.system)}', 'Ihr heimat System')}
|elif event.system = system.name    : {set system to OneOf('{(event.system)}', 'dieses System')}
|else                               : {set system to OneOf('system {(event.system)}' '{(event.system)}'))}
}

{if event.newstate != 'None':
  {_ System has entered a new state}
  {OneOf('Lokale Übertragungen berichten, dass', 'Information: ', 'Transmission abgefangen.  Inhalt lautet: ')}
  {  if event.newstate = 'Boom'        : {OneOf('{system} is experiencing a commercial boom',
  										'{system} is entering a period of hightened commercial success')}
  |elif event.newstate = 'Bust'        : {system} is experiencing economic hardship
  |elif event.newstate = 'Civil Unrest': {OneOf('{system} is experiencing civil unrest',
  										'there is unrest in the {system} system')}
  |elif event.newstate = 'Civil War'   : {OneOf('{system} is at war with another faction in the same system',
  										'civil war has broken out in {system}',
  										'{system} has fallen in to civil war', 'hostilities have broken out in {system}')}
  |elif event.newstate = 'Election'    : {system} is undergoing elections
  |elif event.newstate = 'Expansion'   : {OneOf("a faction in {system}'s is attempting to expand in to a neighbouring system",
  										"a faction in {system}'s is preparing to expand in to a neighbouring system")}
  |elif event.newstate = 'Famine'      : {system} is suffering from famine
  |elif event.newstate = 'Investment'  : {system}'s controlling faction are investing heavily in their local infrastructure
  |elif event.newstate = 'Lockdown'    : {system} has hightened security due to a lockdown by the controlling faction
  |elif event.newstate = 'Outbreak'    : {system} is suffering from an outbreak of contagious disease
  |elif event.newstate = 'Retreat'     : {system}'s controlling faction is retreating from a neighbouring system
  |elif event.newstate = 'War'         : {system} is now at war with a neighbouring system
  |else                                : {OneOf('{system} has entered {event.state}',
  										'{system} is now in a state of {event.state}')}
  }.
}

{_ Triggered when there is a change in the state of a watched system.

- match		The name of the pattern that this event matched
- system	The name of the system
- oldstate	The old state of the system
- newstate	The new state of the system _}

